The paper deals with object discovery from unlabeled driving videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a generic object tracker and evaluates different feature representations and clustering strategies, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with video data, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia), and the dataset released by the authors can be used for information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
